both an update to Debian Sarge (3.1r6, henceforth to be oldstable) and a
new stable release (Debian 4.0, which was codenamed Etch) — and announce
the results of the election for Debian Project Leader — all within 12
hours. Sarge was updated late on April 7th UTC, Sam Hocevar was announced
as DPL at about 00:30 UTC, and preparations for the release of Debian
Etch are ongoing and look good for later on the 8th."

