[0]ZJMX writes "Microsoft is going through its email and phone lists
asking people to [1]support their opposition to California A.B. 1668 —
'Open Document Format, Open Source' — by writing to the California
Assemblymen involved in this bill (contact info in the link). Apparently
they fear that California will join Massachusetts in wanting documents
based on open standards in their government. Let's see if this community
can raise as much support for the California ODF bill as Microsoft can
raise opposition."

