|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/08/1528217              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

jcatcw writes "Mike Elgan argues that the the real reason that cell
phones calls are not allowed is [0]fear of crowd control problems if
calls are allowed during flight. Also, the airlines like keeping
passengers ignorant about ground conditions. The two public reasons,
interference with other systems, could easily be tested, but neither the
FAA nor the FCC manage to do such testing."

