| Zero-60 in 3.1 Seconds, Batteries Included                         |
|   from the i-even-like-the-color dept.                             |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday April 08, @13:51 (Power)                |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/08/1643252     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]FloatsomNJetsom writes "Popular Mechanics has a very cool video and
report about test-driving Hybrid Technologies' L1X-75, [1]a battery
powered, 600-hp, carbon-fiber roadster that pulls zero-60 in about 3.1
seconds, and tops out at 175 mph. Of course, there are few creature
comforts inside, but that's mainly because the car's 200 mile range is
meant for the track, not the road. Nonetheless, Popular Mechanics takes
the car for a spin up 10th Avenue in NYC. Oh, and the car recharges via a
110 outlet. They also [2]test-drove Ford's HySeries Edge, a hydrogen
fuel-cell powered, plug-in series hybrid that, unlike the L1X-75, is
unfortunately at least 10 years away from production and nearly 100 mph
slower."

