| Patti Santangelo v. RIAA May Be Over                               |
|   from the keep-the-faith-kids dept.                               |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday April 08, @16:11 (Music)                |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/08/1838204          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]newtley writes "Odds are that Patti Santangelo, the RIAA case
defendant and New York mother who has made a determined stand against the
Big 4, may have [1]won her battle to clear her name. She and her lawyer,
Jordan Glass, have signed and submitted a stipulation to dismiss with
prejudice the case lodged against her by the RIAA. US federal district
court judge Colleen McMahon's language had earlier seemed to indicate it
was time to end the farce, and the court had the power to entertain a
motion for legal fees. Unfortunately, her two children are still 'in the
line of fire' in the court room."

